    "comment": "Rationale: Tsc2+/- hippocampal pyramidal neurons transfected at DIV 21 with EGFP showed immature spines ( more long, thin filopodia) compared the WT. Quantification showed the Tsc2 mutation reduced the width of dendritic protrusions and increased their length.. Experimental description: 24/09/2018 Pim\n- \"In this study, we used spontaneous Tsc2-mutated Eker rats as animal models of TSC11. We first compared dendritic spine morphology of cultured hippocampal neurons of wild type (WT) and heterozygous Eker (Tsc2+/-) rats. At 21 days in vitro (DIV), the dendritic spines of WT neurons displayed mushroom-type spines (Fig. 1a)(top), whereas the dendrites of Tsc2+/- neuron\"",
